  <div class="story-body">
        <p class="body-text">The highest salaries per agency (paid per annum) vary greatly. Many community boards are on the lower end of this scale, while large city government agencies such as the Law Department, Office of the Actuary, and the Campaign Finance Board are on the higher end of this scale.</p>
        <p class="body-text">19 out of the lowest 20 max salaries are from community boards. On the other hand, six of the agencies with the highest max salaries are related to education in some way. The lowest max salary is from the Manhattan Community Board at $50,000. The highest max salary is from the Department of Ed Pedagogical, at $345,000 (this also references the top paid person in the entire public sector per annum).</p>
